Sponsored by Hibiki Whisky

In the studio of renowned washi artist Eriko Horiki, harmony emerges as a delicate interplay of materials, centuries of Japanese tradition, and acceptance that nature will guide the artist’s hand.

Horiki’s artistic practice is just one facet explored in a new interactive narrative considering what harmony means today and how masters of craft and intentional living achieve this vital balance.

Explore the full experience here: https://businessinsider.com/sc/24-moments-of-harmony 

And learn more about The House of Suntory at https://www.youtube.com/@TheHouseOfSuntory
